      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZARI EXACT (1) finished fifth last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 278m at Launceston, taking a Grade 3/4 in an outstanding 16.01. Has the ability and looks a key chance again. TAKES TIME (7) goes very well this course and distance starting seven times for three wins and three minors. Placed last time (19.66) at this track in a Grade 4/5, finishing third and beaten 2 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. ANGRY MAC (2) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing sixth (23.38) in a Grade 5 at Richmond. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. Great chance to atone. KIWI ICE CUBE (3) is always hard to beat when she races at this trip.",
